post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_15584561_15584643_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 0.9565217391304348, "section_id": 5860}}, "n3337": {"so_15584561_15584643_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 0.9565217391304348, "section_id": 5630}}, "n4659": {"so_15584561_15584643_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 0.9565217391304348, "section_id": 7339}}}, "15584561": {"ViewCount": "686", "Body": "<p>What is the actual effect of the following construct:</p>\n<pre><code>class Base { /* ... */ };\n\ntemplate&lt;class T&gt;\nclass Derived : public T { /* ... */ };\n\nint main() {\n    Derived&lt;const Base&gt; d;\n    // ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Does the <code>Derived</code> class only have access to the <code>const</code>-part of the interface of <code>Base</code>? My first tests indicate that there's actually no effect at all. Why?</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "15584643", "Title": "Effects of a const base class", "CreationDate": "2013-03-23T07:50:01.853", "Id": "15584561", "CommentCount": "2", "PostTypeId": "1", "ClosedDate": "2013-03-27T14:21:54.677", "LastActivityDate": "2013-03-24T09:19:26.893", "Score": "9", "OwnerUserId": "71051", "Tags": "<c++><const><derived-class>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "15584643": {"Id": "15584643", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>My guess is that the <code>const</code> is ignored, because if you try to write</p>\n<pre><code>class Derived : public const Base\n</code></pre>\n<p>the program <a href=\"http://ideone.com/JLJCVV\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">doesn't compile</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>EDIT:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/599926/frozenkoi\">frozenkoi</a> gave the relevant part of the standard in the comments:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_15584561_15584643_0\">\"A typedef-name (7.1.3) that names a class type, or a cv-qualified version thereof, is also a class-name. If a typedef-name that names a cv-qualified class type is used where a class-name is required, the cv-qualifiers are ignored. A typedef-name shall not be used as the identifier in a class-head.\" \u00a79.1</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "LastActivityDate": "2013-03-24T09:19:26.893", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2013-03-23T08:00:45.747", "ParentId": "15584561", "CommentCount": "6", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T10:32:04.783", "OwnerUserId": "1225541"}});